    <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
        <body>
            <div xml:id="KT379-kilavi">
                <p type="edition">notumalar varaivuḻit tōḻi aṟattoṭu niṉṟatu. </p>


                <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">The confidante standing firm in duty, when the
                    marriage with strangers [is imminent]. </p>
            </div>

            <div xml:id="KT379">
                <lg type="edition">
                    <l> iṉṟiyāṇ ṭaiyaṉō tōḻi kuṉṟattup</l>
                    <l> paḻaṅkuḻi yakaḻnta kāṉavaṉ kiḻaṅkiṉoṭu</l>
                    <l> kaṇṇakaṉ ṟūmaṇi peṟūu nāṭa</l>
                    <l> ṉaṟivukāḻk koḷḷu maḷavaic ciṟutoṭi</l>
                    <l> yemmil varukuvai nīyeṉa</l>
                    <l> pomma lōti nīvi yōṉē.</l>


                </lg>

                <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                    <l> Where [is] he today, friend,</l>
                    <l> who stroked [my] thick hair,</l>
                    <l> saying “you will come to our house,</l>
                    <l rend="indent3"> [you with] small bracelets, when knowledge is ripe”, <note place="foot"> In other words when the secret relation is no longer secret. Differently Cām.: when HER knowledge has come to maturity, that is, the message is a consolation directed to a girl not yet of age. </note> </l>
                    <l> the man from a land,</l>
                    <l rend="indent"> where the forest man, who has dug a pit for fruit <note place="foot">
                        <term xml:lang="ta">  paḻam = paḻaiya </term>    "old", as read by Cām., does not make sense. It rather might be read either as an adverb to <term xml:lang="ta">   akaḻnta </term>      (a pit dug successfully) or attributive to  <term xml:lang="ta"> kuḻi </term> : a "fruit pit", that is, a pit which actually does contain something. </note>    on the hill,</l>
                <l rend="indent"> [and] obtains, together with the bulbous roots, a jewel</l>
                <l rend="indent8"> of eye-widening    <note place="foot">
                    <term xml:lang="ta"> kaṇ akal </term>   : T.V.G. explains this as a jewel of broad area, i.e. a big jewel. </note>  purity.</l>


        </lg>
    </div>
</body>
